          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Boating Capacity Standards Act of 2015</b></p> <p> Directs the Commandant of the Coast Guard to: </p> <ul> <li> establish standards for determining the maximum passenger capacity for recreational vessels, expressed in the number of passengers and in pounds; </li> <li> require manufacturers and operators of passenger vessels to permanently display such maximum capacity in a legible manner that is clearly visible to passengers; and </li> <li> require operators to post notice of the need to balance vessel weight to avoid capsizing. </li> </ul> <p>Defines a &quot;recreational vehicle&quot; as any vessel that is manufactured or used primarily for pleasure, excluding any vessel that is subject to Coast Guard inspection and engaged in commercial use.</p>]]></text>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2015-06-04T21:27:05Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
